description:
I've yet to dig into it yet, but it took some time to get it to launch in Ubuntu 22

I've been able to implement a patch so far by editing the file "/usr/share/manuskript/manuskript/functions/__init__.py". On line 197 I changed:

return QColor(r, g, b) if not fromString else QColor(r, g, b).name()

to

return QColor(int(r), int(g), int(b)) if not fromString else QColor(int(r), int(g), int(b)).name()
